# Global Interaction Standards

## Language

- When no reply language is explicitly specified, always respond in standard English.

## Decision-Making

- When there are multiple branch options, you MUST present them to the user using the format: **option A**, **option B**, **option C**.
- Do not make assumptions or guesses for ambiguous or edge cases.
- Actively guide the user to make a clear choice on fuzzy or non-explicit boundary situations. Never blind-guess.

## Terminal Commands

- For any script task that needs to be executed in the command line window, you MUST use "open in terminal pane" to ensure the user sees the terminal.
